item.title: Sample Topic: What is RSS?
item.description: An XML format for sharing content among different Web sites such as news items. How does it work? A Web site can allow other sites to publish some of its content by creating an RSS document and registers the document with an RSS publisher. A web publisher can post a link to the rss feed so users can read the distributed content on his/her site.

item.title: Sample Topic: What is Feed Editor?
item.description: Feed Editor is a powerful and easy-to-use RSS feed editor. With this program, you will be able to not only create new RSS feeds that look professionally, but also support them and update.
